#: includes/class-pressark-privacy.php:53
msgid "PressArk stores the following personal data in custom database tables on your server:"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-pressark-privacy.php:56
msgid "<strong>Chat conversations</strong> — message content, titles, and timestamps."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-pressark-privacy.php:57
msgid "<strong>Action log</strong> — records of actions performed through the assistant (action type, target, timestamp)."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-pressark-privacy.php:58
msgid "<strong>Execution runs</strong> — transient server-side state for in-flight requests (route, status, timestamps). Automatically cleaned up within hours to days."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-pressark-privacy.php:59
msgid "<strong>Background tasks</strong> — queued async operations and their results. Automatically cleaned up within hours to days."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-pressark-privacy.php:60
msgid "<strong>Scheduled automations</strong> — automation configurations including prompt text, schedule, execution metadata, and notification destinations."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-pressark-privacy.php:61
msgid "<strong>Notification settings</strong> — Telegram chat ID stored as user meta when Telegram notifications are enabled."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-pressark-privacy.php:64
msgid "PressArk also stores <strong>operational billing telemetry</strong> (token usage, cost estimates, provider/model metadata) in a cost ledger table. This data is linked to your user ID and is erased on request, but is not included in personal data exports as it is operational in nature."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-pressark-privacy.php:66
msgid "Chat messages, screen context, and content excerpts are sent to the configured AI provider (OpenRouter, OpenAI, Anthropic, DeepSeek, or Google Gemini) to generate responses."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-pressark-privacy.php:68
msgid "In bundled billing mode, PressArk contacts the PressArk license server with your license key, your site domain, and a SHA-256 hash of your site domain to validate your plan. The PressArk token-bank service receives your site domain, a numeric user identifier, and token-usage totals to enforce plan limits."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-pressark-privacy.php:70
msgid "In BYOK (Bring Your Own Key) mode, AI requests are sent directly to your chosen provider. No data is sent to PressArk services for AI billing."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-pressark-privacy.php:72
msgid "PressArk builds a local full-text index of published content in a custom database table. This is site content, not personal data, and does not leave your server except as context included in AI requests."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-pressark-privacy.php:74
msgid "If Telegram notifications are enabled for automations, your Telegram chat ID and bot token are stored encrypted. Notification messages are sent via the Telegram Bot API and may include summaries of actions performed."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-pressark-privacy.php:77
msgid "PressArk applies configurable retention policies: action logs (default 90 days), chat history (default 180 days), cost telemetry (default 365 days). Execution runs and background tasks are automatically cleaned up on shorter cycles (hours to days). You can adjust retention periods in PressArk Settings."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-pressark-privacy.php:79
msgid "All API keys are encrypted at rest using Sodium authenticated encryption (XSalsa20-Poly1305). When the plugin is uninstalled, all plugin data (tables, options, transients, user meta, and scheduled events) is removed."
msgstr ""

